cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.NA, cs.CC, cs.SI 

This paper discusses a combinatorial algorithm for computing regularization paths, which is a common topic in machine learning and optimization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of graph theory and combinatorial optimization, which suggests the categories cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as possible sub-categories as well.
